      • TreeSelectionEvent

        public TreeSelectionEvent(Object source,
                          TreePath[] paths,
                          boolean[] areNew,
                          TreePath oldLeadSelectionPath,
                          TreePath newLeadSelectionPath)
        Represents a change in the selection of a TreeSelectionModel.
        Parameters:
        source - The source of the event.
        paths - The paths whose selection state has changed.
        areNew - Boolean for each path that indicates if the path is new to the selection (true) or has been removed from the selection (false).
        oldLeadSelectionPath - The old lead selection path.
        newLeadSelectionPath - The new lead selection path.

      • TreeSelectionEvent

        Represents a change in the selection of a TreeSelectionModel.
        Parameters:
        source - The source of the event.
        path - The path whose selection state has changed.
        isNew - true if the path has been added to the selection, false if removed.
        oldLeadSelectionPath - The old lead selection path.
        newLeadSelectionPath - The new lead selection path.
